Chapter One
Deceit and Flattery
This was said by the Buddha the Perfected One that is what I heard
Mendicants this spiritual life is not lived for the sake of deceiving people or flattering them nor for the benefit of possessions honor or popularity nor thinking So let people know about me
This spiritual life is lived for the sake of restraint and giving up
That is what the Buddha said
On this it is said
The Buddha taught the spiritual life
not because of tradition
but for the sake of restraint and giving up
and because it culminates in extinguishment
This is the path followed by the great souls
the great hermits
Those who practice it
as it was taught by the Buddha
doing the teachers bidding
make an end of suffering
This too was spoken by the Blessed One that is what I heard
