Chapter One
Mortifying
This was said by the Buddha the Perfected One that is what I heard
These two things mendicants are mortifying
Its when someone hasnt done good and skillful things that keep them safe but has done bad violent and depraved things
Thinking I havent done good things theyre mortified Thinking I have done bad things theyre mortified
These are the two things that are mortifying
That is what the Buddha said
On this it is said
Having done bad things
by way of body
speech and mind
and whatever else is corrupt
not having done good deeds
and having done many bad
when their body breaks up that witless person
is reborn in hell
This too was spoken by the Blessed One that is what I heard
