The Chapter on the Holy Offering of the Teaching
This was said by the Buddha the Perfected One that is what I heard
Mendicants those mendicants who are deceivers stubborn flatterers frauds insolent and scattered they are no mendicants of mine
Theyve left this teaching and training and they dont achieve growth improvement or maturity in this teaching and training
But those mendicants who are genuine not flatterers wise amenable and serene they are mendicants of mine
They havent left this teaching and training and they do achieve growth improvement or maturity in this teaching and training
That is what the Buddha said
On this it is said
Those who are deceivers stubborn flatterers and frauds
insolent and scattered
these dont grow in the teaching
that was taught by the perfected Buddha
But those who are genuine not flatterers wise
amenable and serene
these do grow in the teaching
that was taught by the perfected Buddha
This too was spoken by the Blessed One that is what I heard
So It Was Said
